                <h1>Expert Tips for Hanging Wallpaper Effortlessly</h1>
                <p>To hang wallpaper successfully, start by prepping the walls: clean, patch, and prime if necessary. Measure and cut the wallpaper strips with precision, leaving some extra for adjustments. Use a wallpaper paste or pre-pasted wallpaper for easy application. Align the top of the strip, smooth it from the center outward, and ensure there are no air bubbles. Trim excess at the bottom for a clean finish.</p>
